As part of the netball season preparations, PEPPS Preparatory School and College teams recently attended a netball clinic that was held at the school.
The clinic was used to equip future professional netball players with crucial skills that included attacking, defensive and live game situations.
The participating schools challenged one another during evening games.
PEPPS Communication and Marketing officer Millisa Naidoo emphasised that the clinic deemed to be beneficial to all who attended, gaining an improved knowledge on the game and building self-confidence.
She applauded players from PEPPS as she indicated that the school was proud of their determination and outstanding performance.
Story: ENDY SENYATSI
